title: Mobiola Webcam for Symbian S60v3 eg Nokia N95 - Use your phone a
description:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~RAPIDSHARE MIRROR~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Turn your Symbian smartphone into a high-quality wireless Bluetooth-based web camera and throw out your bulky USB webcam. Very simple to install and configure, Mobiola Web Camera for S60 3rd Edition 1.0 consists of two software components: (1) a client application that resides on the phone, and (2) a webcam PC driver compatible with any Windows application that can receive video feeds from a web camera including Skype, Yahoo, MSN, AOL IM, ICQ messangers,and www.grouper.com. Carry your webcam with you wherever you go and connect it to your laptop at anytime, no wires necessary. Try it now and experience resolution and frame rates comparable to some of the top-performing USB webcams on the market! UIQ version and S60 2nd Edition version are also available. Mobiola Web Camera works only with 32-bit PC systems yet. Stay tuned for Windows Mobile version, versions with USB and WiFi support and support for 64-bit PC systems.

Requirements
8 MB of free disk space on PC, 300kb of free phone memory, 1Mb of free run time memory

Compatible with any Symbian S60v3 device e.g. all Nokia N-seres and E-series (except N70) and some others. Windows PC with Bluetooth connection.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~INSTRUCTIONS~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. Install Warelex.Mobiola.... sis file onto your phone as you would any other app.
If you have "Expired Certificate" error set your phones date back to 1 January 2007, then change back after installation.

2. Install the software on your PC.

3. Choose a COM port (can be changed later)

4. Enter serial code on PC software IMEI 353252012313615 SERIAL SSK4-AW73-HKE3-FNFA

5. Run software on phone, and select connect, then select your pc from devices list.

6. Hide the application and run MSN or your chosen webcam software, your phone should now be available as a source
